summary:
We prove uniqueness results and Harnack inequality for Bessel operators
  \begin{align*}
  %\label{def L transf alpha}
  D_t-\Delta_{x} -2a\cdot\nabla_xD_y- D_{yy}- \frac cy D_y
  % \nonumber
\\[1ex]&=y^{\alpha}\sum_{i,j=1}^{N+1}a_{ij}D_{ij}+y^{\alpha-1}\left(v,\nabla\right)-by^{\alpha-2}.
  \end{align*}
  in the strip $[0,T]\times \mathbb{R}^{N+1}_+=\{0 \leq t \leq T, x \in
\mathbb{R}^N, y>0\}$ under Neumann boundary conditions at $y=0$.
